                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There are two situations in which a MOB will not attack a PET (charmed or summoned).
<br />

<br />
(1) There is a PLAYER in the MOB's melee range.
<br />

<br />
(2) There are more than FOUR THINGS on the MOB's hate list (THINGS includes PLAYERs and PETs).
<br />

<br />
When I play my Cleric, I often charm duo with a Druid in Storms.  We charm a frog pet, and it can tank with no problem, with me healing it during the battle.  I can even send in my hammer pet.  (This means there are 3-4 things on the mob's hate list, depending on whether I have cast my hammer or not).
<br />

<br />
Sometimes, we have an Enchanter.  In that case, the Enchanter and Druid *both* have a pet attacking the mob.  In this situation, I can not use my hammer pet, and I can not heal during the battle.  If I do heal during the battle, there will be 5 things on the mob's hate list, and a pet can no longer tank.  At this point, whichever of the 3 players has the most agro will be summoned.
<br />

<br />
There.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ceilon and Hawafena
<br />
Night Elf Hunter and Pretty Green Spider
<br />
Argent Dawn (East Coast RP)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
