hmm ok i'm confused here
<br />
from my understanding they added a rule on charm aggro, 4 or so on aggro list=RANDOM charmed pet holds no aggro. i have not tested DC but i'm almost positive this aggro rule does not apply to dc.
<br />
i have seen this happen a lot. while doing armorer camp in tatics once i sent in pet, held aggro fine, it tanked it without heal (was hasted) till named was around 20%, then grp would run in to save pet, we'd all get in aggro range and pet instently losses aggro to random targets, sk never gets a chance to cast or get in range before healers start dieing cause it's totally loss aggro. someone healed the pet luckily and when it was down to me and two others pet instently had aggro again and held it like a glove and named died, this happened exactly teh same way on two diffrent named (you'd think they have learned the first time when i tried to explain what happened)
<br />

<br />
seen this happen in HoH duoing witha  ranger and we wanted to invite more but didn't have a powerful enough healer to use a tank, get 3people+me+pet and we'd be perma rooting.
<br />

<br />
when this rule was applied a druid and I did PoD a lot (gained like 3 lvls doing this over a few weeks) and second this rule was put in when both our pets were on a mob and it was only the two of us in the area we had to keep them rooted or we'd be aggro kitting even if we didn't cast on the mob at all and just sent in pet (we were both standing of course)
<br />

<br />
the way i understood it was 2 people(or a person and their pet)+enchanter(or other charm class)+pet was max that could be on mobs aggro list. having a person fd works as well, just as long as they stay fd during the whole fight, he stand sup pet holds no aggro again.
<br />

<br />
this applies ot random charm only, DC has almost the exact rules as a normal pet does. random charm pet losses all aggro when more then 3people+charmed pet are on aggro list and will regain all lost aggro when that limit is back. of course if anyone is within melee range of the mobs they will be swung at same way any pet works</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=319303" target="_blank" class="postlink">Olmec</a> <span style="font-style: italic">Let Them Come</span>
