                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't know if the 4 person (either pets or players) rule applies to summoned pets but I do know this. The 4 person agro rule is in the game. It applies to using a charmed pet as a tank. If you do not believe me and the many others who have experienced this then try this little experiment. It can be done with green con mobs so it is 100% safe. Charm a mob, sic it on another and have more than 4 players/pets agro the mob your charmed pet is tanking. Have them cast low agro spells such as level 1 or level 4 nukes or heal the pet with a very minor heal spell. I guarantee that as soon as the 5th player/pet is on the mobs hate list it will ignore the charmed pet that is tanking it and run after players. Keep in mind this applies only to having over 4 people on the hate list at the same time. If someone or a pet dies and another comes in afterwards and gets on the hate list you will not get summoned.
<br />

<br />
Forget for a moment this was even mentioned in a patch when it went live. Don't go calling what everyone knows for a fact BS when you have incomplete knowledge of the esituation at hand. This change was to stop players from using charmed pets to gimp certain encounters such as the wing and tower mini bosses in the Bastion of Thunder.
<br />

<br />
Most of the players who are concerned with the 4 pet agro rule for pet tanking are in the higher levels where a summoned pet will last in the number of seconds even on a slowed mob. They will not be able to use summoned pets for tanking at all, thus if they use a pet for tanking, they are referring to charmed pets.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
