                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">** Charm Changes **
<br />

<br />
- Healing a charmed pet now generates an appropriate amount of hate for the healer.
<br />
- Charmed pets now take up to one third of the experience for each NPC killed.  This amount scales down based on the percentage of damage to the target that the pet does. Dire charm pets still take the same experience they always have.
<br />
- Charmed pets are no longer selected as a monster's preferred target if there are many players available for the monster to attack instead.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
From the 08 April 2003 patch message (a date which will live in infamy).  I usually try to stay low on the aggro list when dealing with people who don't quite get the rule of 4 until they get splattered a few times.  Almost nobody who isn't already familiar with the rule gets it the first time i explain it to them in a charming situation without at least one death.
<br />

<br />
Does anyone know how fd players work with the rule of 4?  I haven't had a chance to test whether fd removes a player from the list for the purposes of pets tanking.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
