                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the confusion here is the way the situation is described.
<br />

<br />
For example, if your group is comprised of 4 things (including whatever pet type), and a pet happens to be the agro leader, and a 5th thing is added, the pet is forced from the top. (most likely to the bottom of the list)
<br />

<br />

<br />
If you begin with more than 5, and the pet gets agro, then he will remain on top the list.
<br />

<br />
I could be wrong, but I believe the way this works is, that, in the first situation, the pet STILL could gain agro, but because he is bumped from the top to the bottom, he will never out agro the rest on the list.
<br />

<br />
In the second case, where 5 or more are set on the list from the beginning, even tho initially, the pet gets bumped to the bottom, everyone is relatively close together still on the list, and the pet can quickly regain the top spot.
<br />

<br />
Also, I believe it bumps the top position if it is a pet only when a 5th thing is added to the list, but the next up could also be a pet, so it appears as iff nothing happened.
<br />

<br />
This is my theory <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
