                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From experience if a pet does not start with agro and there are 5 or more on the mob's hate list, the pet will NEVER gain agro (while 5 or more are on the hate list).  This goes from the newbie snakes to the 1200+ hitters in GoD.  The reasoning behind it is simple.  EQ is coded so that as soon as more than 4 are on a mob's hate list it will not attack a pet.  The exception to this is if root is applied.  Then proximity agro takes over.  
<br />

<br />
If a pet starts with agro and 5 or more get onto the mob's hatelist, the mob will agro the player with the highest agro.  The rule of 4 is in effect and does apply for pets (charmed or summoned).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />&lt;DIV&gt;
<br />
&lt;MAP NAME="sig1"&gt;
<br />
