<br />

<br />
Actually rethinking the situation, I believe there IS a way around it.  I believe I had asked the Druid to hold off sending in her DC pet until my DC pet had killed off around 15% of mobs health.  At that point the only ones on the aggro list were:
<br />

<br />
Chanter + Chanter DC + Cleric.
<br />

<br />
Then once she engaged her pet it quickly became 2nd on the list of aggro, so at this point it stood at this:
<br />

<br />
Chanter + Chanter DC + Druid DC + Cleric.
<br />

<br />
Then she would lay in her DoT's in which the initial DC pet would not lose aggro, he would retain it.  So we were still at the 5 on aggro, but because my DC pet had built such a large amount of aggro initially, It never broke off.  Now if I sat, then it would come after me.  
<br />

<br />
So, this leaves me wondering if the rule of 5 only decreases the amount of aggro on the pet, and not deletes it entirely.
<br />

<br />
Omni</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
