                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Tried something for the hell of it this week.  Pet Tanking Vindi.
<br />

<br />
First attempt:
<br />

<br />
2 Chanters with buffed DC pets
<br />
Ranger pulled without appropriate warning/instruction, Vindi ping-pongs when second pet engages (4 limit hate list rule)
<br />
Result:  Wipe
<br />

<br />
Second attempt:
<br />
The 4 limit rule now explained to raid, and the gimpness of 10Kish pets trying to tank vindi without heals, I convince the raid to take another approach:
<br />

<br />
2 Chanters Beckon 2 PoZs
<br />
I pet-pull vindi on the bridge
<br />
Both pets engage, pet 2 starts healing pet 1 (woohoo)
<br />
Vindi 90 pct - Guardians come to his aid out of no where (we had killed them earlier on first attempt)
<br />
I tash and pull 1 guardian off, root it.
<br />
Ranger calls "off tank"
<br />
I say "NOOOO"
<br />
Raid engages guardian, Vindi (must be linked to hate list cause he was a good distance away) ping-pongs.
<br />

<br />
Result:  Wipe
<br />

<br />
We learned from the first attempt and had a rezzer camped at least.
<br />

<br />
Was great fun nonetheless.
<br />

<br />
Anyone do this (post-nerf) successfully?</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nokei Orhaste &lt;Retired&gt; E66.191/L h++ 2.8khp 4.6km ft12 BK10</a></span>
